## What NOT to change

- Algorithmic constants mirroring upstream Python: 5% mask threshold, 5 PCA
  components, `refsize=300`, `maskrepeats=5`, `zscore=5`, `alpha=1e-4`.
- KNN global-vs-local index semantics (documented in AGENTS.md).
- Upstream bug replications: CPA +1 overcount, last-bin drop.
- The `G=2, modelNames="V"` GMM default — expose as a parameter (done) but
  do not change the default.
- Any Rcpp C++ code (`src/knn_reference.cpp`, `src/nipter_matching.cpp`).
- `bam_convert()` DuckDB/SQL logic in `convert.R`.
- `bam_convert_npz()` Python/reticulate path — conformance-only.
